                        "content": "The nurse is creating a plan of care for the client with multiple myeloma and includes which priority intervention in the plan?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "49d86bb4d5071eb7de614d6c79f7abfb",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Creating创新",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nHypercalcemia caused by bone destruction is a priority concern in the client with multiple myeloma. The nurse would administer fluids in adequate amounts to maintain a urine output of 1.5 to 2 L/day; this requires about 3 L of fluid intake per day. The fluid is needed not only to dilute the calcium overload but also to prevent protein from precipitating in the renal tubules. Options 2, 3, and 4 may be components of the plan of care but are not the priority in this client.",
                        "id": "e6fe4a63a9e640179266fbdd5a3e0c7e",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "6f3126fbfdaf419baa9884cf5941e154",
                                "content": "Pathological fracture"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "5522c7651dcf4e60b3a13d15db18bb76",
                                "content": "Urinalysis positive for Bence Jones protein"
                            },
                            {
